## the new constraints

```
PROJECT: FUNDAMENTAL_THEOREM_OF_ALGEBRA

CENTROID
  Every non-constant polynomial over ℂ has a root.
  Proof via π₁(S¹):
  - Assume p(z) has no root.
  - Construct map f(z) = p(z)/|p(z)| on large circle R.
  - For large R, degree(f) = degree(p) = n.
  - Map extends to disk (since no root), so is null-homotopic.
  - Therefore degree(f) = 0.
  - Contradiction if n > 0.

AXES
  Mathlib π₁ infrastructure ↔ Polynomial API
  Topological proof ↔ Algebraic statement
  
SATELLITES
  $\pi_1(S^1) \cong \mathbb{Z}$ (DONE - Base)
  Winding Number Homomorphism (DONE - Tool)
  Polynomial Asymptotics (Standard Mathlib)
  Continuous extension from S¹ to D² (Standard Topology)
```

